<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1" standalone="no"?> 
<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../manrev.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>fr</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>modulo  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>April 1993  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="modulo"> reste arithmétique symétrique modulo m  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="pmodulo"> reste arithmétique positif modulo m  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>i=modulo(n,m)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>i=pmodulo(n,m)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
  <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>n</PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION><SP>: entier</SP></PARAM_DESCRIPTION>

  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
 <PARAM_NAME>m</PARAM_NAME>
 <PARAM_DESCRIPTION><SP>: entier</SP></PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
  </PARAM_ITEM>

  </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    <VERB>modulo</VERB> calcule <VERB>i= n (modulo m)</VERB> c&apos;est à dire le reste de <VERB>n</VERB> divisé par <VERB>m</VERB> (<VERB>n</VERB> et <VERB>m</VERB> sont entiers).
  </P>
  <P>
     i = n - m .* int (n ./ m). Ici la réponse peut être négative si <VERB>n</VERB> et/ou <VERB>m</VERB> 
    sont négatifs.
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>pmodulo</VERB> calcule <VERB>i = n - m .* floor (n ./ m)</VERB>, la réponse est positive ou nulle.
  </P>

  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
n=[1,2,10,15];m=[2,2,3,5];
modulo(n,m)

modulo(-3,9)
pmodulo(-3,9)
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
</MAN>
